Graeme Finlay, 53, went on trial after retired engineer Ron Phillips, 70, and his wife June, 69, were knocked unconscious outside their cabin on board the Thomson Celebration cruise ship .
Mr Finlay claimed Mr Phillips threw a cup of hot chocolate at him, swore and struck him with his crutch .
He said: 'It's been hell, I really am, but I told the truth in the court and I'm thankful that the jury believed me'